<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="58" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d58">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source"><persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2" type="from">Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RE1" type="to">Roosevelt</persName></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d58fn1">Apparently sent via military channels.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-26">26 October 1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><gloss target="#t_FormerNavalPerson1">Former Naval Person</gloss> to
                            President personal and most secret number 475 your number 396.<note n="2" xml:id="d58fn2"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_39">p. 39</ref>.</note></p>
                        <p>1. I shall be delighted to meet you anywhere in North Africa, but I hope
                            we need not wait till the twentieth. Strongly recommend sea voyage to
                                <gloss target="#t_Anfa1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Anfa</hi></gloss>
                            which we know, moving on to Pyramids if and when convenient. By all
                            means ask <persName corresp="#p_CKS1">Chiang</persName>. If <gloss target="#t_UJ1">UJ</gloss> refuses, then <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName>
                            <pb facs="0134" n="42" xml:id="pg_42"/> with a Russian military mission
                            would do. It seems to me fine progress has been made by <persName corresp="#p_HC1">Hull</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> at Moscow and still more on the Russian southern
                            front.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Prime</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>